quran[9]{c,v,t,f}:
  23,85,"They will say: "
  23,86,"Say: "
  23,87,"They will say: "
  25,31,"Thus have We made for every Prophet an enemy among the Mujrimûn (disbelievers, polytheists, criminals). But Sufficient is your Lord as a Guide and Helper."
  25,32,"And those who disbelieve say: "
  25,33,"And no example or similitude do they bring (to oppose or to find fault in you or in this Qur’ân), but We reveal to you the truth (against that similitude or example), and the better explanation thereof."
  26,4,"If We will, We could send down to them from the heaven a sign, to which they would bend their necks in humility."
  26,5,"And never comes there unto them a Reminder as a recent revelation from the Most Gracious (Allâh), but they turn away therefrom."
  26,6,"So they have indeed denied (the truth - this Qur’ân), then the news of what they mocked at will come to them."